fields.description: Here is a masterpiece that Stephin Merritt made. I think it may be my favorite Magnetic Fields song.
Utterly, heartbreakingly beautiful. And catchy to boot!
Seems basically impossible to pick a single favorite Kate Bush song but... if I had to it would be this one. The octave jump in her vocals in the chorus is just perfection.
Scary, twisted post-punk at its very best.
How about we follow up that last spooky post-punk song with of Montreal's early, queer-Beatles stuff. Isn't it just so lovely <3
A beautiful, lush, constantly driving forward instrumental.
